[A] Afghanistan
Date: Thu 24 Dec 2020 01:34 PM AFT
Source: Khaama Press [abridged, edited]
https://www.khaama.com/afghanistan-reports-234-new-covid-19-cases-in-24-hours-334433/


The Ministry of Public Health reported on [Thu 24 Dec 2020] that, out of 2568 samples, 234 cases have turned positive in the last 24 hours. At least 188 860 people have so far been tested in the governmental labs, and there still are 8174 known active cases in the country.

According to the ministry, within 24 hours, 622 individuals have recovered from COVID-19, and 9 individuals are reported dead. The new cases recorded are in Kabul (39), Herat (32), Kandahar (27), Balkh (4), Nangarhar (16), Takhar (12), Baghlan (11), Bamyan (6), Kunduz (10), Nimroz (19), Dykundi (6), Ghazni (1), Logar (2), Badghis (2), Badakhshan (3), Wardak (2), Kapisa (22), Kunar (4), Zabul (1), Uruzgan (2), Faryab (2), Samangan (2), Jawzjan (6), and Sar-e-Pul (3).

The total number of cases in Afghanistan is 51 594, total deaths are 2135 and the total recoveries recorded are 40582.

[byline: Mohammad Haroon Alim]

