[D] Nepal
Date: Thu 24 Dec 2020 4:08 PM NPT
Source: The Himalayan Times [edited]
https://thehimalayantimes.com/nepal/613-new-covid-19-cases-registered-on-thursday-nationwide-tally-hits-256592/


Nepal on [Thu 24 Dec 2020] reported 613 new cases of coronavirus infection from across the country. With this, the nationwide infection count has advanced to 256 592. Of the total cases, 233 are females while 380 are males. In the last 24 hours, 244 cases surfaced in Kathmandu Valley. The capital hosts the highest number of active cases.

Likewise, 739 people who were earlier infected with the virus are reported to have recovered in the past 24 hours as per the latest data provided by health ministry. As of today [23 Dec 2020], 247 400 individuals have recovered from the novel coronavirus infection. The recovery rate, as such, is 96.4 per cent. Nepal's active COVID-19 case count currently stands at 7384. Meanwhile, 5 more fatalities from the disease have taken the total death toll to 1808.

According to the health ministry, 5510 PCR tests were conducted in the last 24 hours. With this, a total of 1 896 250 PCR tests have been carried out in Nepal to date.

Currently, there are 400 individuals in various quarantine facilities across Nepal.

On [Wed 23 Dec 2020], Nepal's coronavirus case count reached 255 979 with 743 newly confirmed cases.

