[The media report has links to the published studies providing the data used in the report. For those who are interested, go to the source URL and click on the provided links.

While the initial thought is that COVID-19 infection was responsible for the increase in stillbirths, the "etiology" is more insidious -- decreased antenatal care. Adding pregnancy outcomes to the collateral damage seen resulting from overwhelmed health services and fear of exposure to the SARS-CoV-2. This saga has not ended and the data are frightening. - Mod.MPP]

