communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In the past 24 hours, the USA (140 000), UK (32 340), and Russia (28 284) have reported the highest numbers of cases. A global total of 7321 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (27 Dec 2020).

Countries reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (8 countries) include the USA, UK, Russia, India (18 574), Brazil (18 479), Turkey (14 205), Germany (12 153), and Canada (10 404). A large number of countries have not reported (including Spain, Switzerland, Sweden, and Costa Rica), or fewer new cases have been reported (United States, Poland, Peru among others).

A total of 44 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 21 of the 44 countries that reported more than 1000 newly confirmed cases are from the European region, 9 are from the Americas region, 8 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 3 are from the South East Asia region, 2 are from the Western Pacific region, and one from the African region. Clearly related to weekend reporting artifact.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have decreased by 12.2%, while daily reported deaths have decreased by 10.4%. Similar comparative 7-day averages in the United States show a 14.6% decrease in daily reported cases and an 11.6% decrease in reported deaths.

Impression: While the global daily reported cases continue to increase with over 400 000 newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours (a considerably lower number of cases reported due to the holiday/weekend effect). Countries in the European and the Americas regions are still showing the largest increases in daily new case counts even with reductions in daily case reports due to the holiday weekend, followed by the Eastern Mediterranean, South East Asia, and Western Pacific regions. South Africa has crossed the 1 million mark for cumulative case reports making it the 18th country to do so. - Mod.MPP]
